<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910909-0151</DOCNO><DOCID>910909-0151.</DOCID><HL>   Law:   Aura Systems, Levitron Settle</HL><DATE>09/09/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   AURA</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)LAW AND LEGAL AFFAIRS (LAW)</IN><NS>LAW andamp; LEGAL ISSUES, HEARINGS, RULINGS, LEGISLATION (LAW)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   EL SEGUNDO, Calif. -- Aura Systems Inc. said a settlementhad been reached in a patent lawsuit filed against thecompany.   The suit, filed by Levitron Inc. of Dallas, had challengedAura's ownership of certain patents and technology rights. Asa result of the settlement, Aura regains 140,000 commonshares that had been issued to Levitron and a groupassociated with it. Aura is involved in magnetic suspensiontechnology, scene projection hardware and advanced computingsystems.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>